Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-buff. Rectangular stamp with caduceus (winged?) symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '327' or '329'. Name Nysios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0394.27.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (204)
